Description:
The Reggiane Innovation Park represents a territorial hub for industrial research and technological transfer, able to stimulate and facilitate collaboration between companies, research laboratories, creatives, and investors. The Innovation Park contributes to identifying potential future challenges and opportunities in the market, working on strategic skills, and creating an “innovation chain”. In this place, education for creativity and change allows the productive world to dialogue and intersect with scientific, technological, and humanistic knowledge.

ADVANTAGES FOR YOUR BUSINESS 
- We support companies to create product and process innovation;
- We offer support programs for innovative start-ups and spin-offs of new businesses;
- We promote institutional relations, partnerships, national and international networks, and clusters;
- We provide services for international projects;
- We develop projects to attract and retain national and international creative skills;
- We organize networking and community building activities to encourage collaboration and hybridization between companies, research centers, and universities.

WHY CHOOSE THE INNOVATION PARK
The Reggiane Innovation Park represents a place of collaboration, innovation, and technology transfer capable of providing a real advantage to all the subjects that gravitate around it by offering: 
- High-quality customizable spaces, made with highly sustainable construction techniques and equipped with smart, functional, and innovative technologies;
- Industrial research and technology transfer laboratories;
- Network of relationships in the territory with schools, Universities, associations, and Public Administration;
- Internationalization services  and support for European projects;
- Hi-Tech companies leading nationally and internationally.

La Société d’Aménagement et de Promotion des Côtes et Zones Touristiques du Sénégal (SAPCO-SENEGAL) est une Société Anonyme à Participation Publique créée en 1975  avec un capital de 1,2 milliard de francs CFA détenu à 98,75% par l’Etat du Sénégal et à 1,25 % par la Société Nationale de Recouvrement (SNR).  Mise en place pour mettre en œuvre l’aménagement touristique de la Petite Côte, la SAPCO-SENEGAL a vu son intervention étendue au niveau national depuis l’élargissement de ses compétences en 2004.

Au terme d’une nouvelle Convention Générale signée le 21 novembre 2013 avec l’Etat du Sénégal, le Gouvernement a assigné à la SAPCO-SENEGAL l’objectif fondamental de créer, de développer et de promouvoir le tourisme.

MISSIONS:
Constitué des Zones d’Intérêt Touristique (ZIT) dans l’ensemble du territoire national pour en assurer la maîtrise foncière;
Immatriculer au nom de l’Etat les ZIT identifiés;
Rechercher des investisseurs nationaux et étrangers susceptibles de financer des projets hôteliers et para hôteliers sur les différents sites identifiés;
Créer sur ces sites des stations touristiques en procédant notamment à la réalisation des aménagements de base (voiries et réseaux divers), d’équipements collectifs et d’un environnement planté;
Céder ou louer des terrains viabilisés ou non viabilisés à des promoteurs ou des gérants qualifiés;
Veiller au respect, par les promoteurs appelés à s’établir sur la zone, des normes et règles d’urbanisme et d’architectures, dans le cadre du plan d’aménagement établi par le gouvernement.
Gérer les stations touristiques en assurant l’entretien des équipements, la .propreté et la salubrité de l’environnement, la sécurité des personnes et des biens, la promotion des investissements pour y attirer un maximum de clientèle et enfin assurer l’animation;
Et généralement, toutes opérations commerciales, financières, immobilières se rattachant directement ou indirectement à cet objectif et susceptibles d’en faciliter la réalisation.

Planning Practice & Research (PPR) has established itself as the source for current research on planning practice - city and regional, town and country, urban or spatial planning. It is intended for reflective, critical academics, professionals and students who are concerned to keep abreast of and challenge current thinking.

PPR is committed to:

- Bridging perspectives across planning research, planning practice and planning education; and between planning, design, engineering and social disciplines;

- Critical evaluation of the contribution of planning practice to creating more
sustainable, resilient and socially just places, in the face of climate change and
illiberal politics;

- Providing a forum for an international readership to share and compare research and experiences on planning practice between countries and cultures;

- Presenting research in an accessible, succinct style, not overly theoretical, but analytical.

- Giving opportunities and support to practitioners and those new to publishing to share their work with the academic planning community.

PPR has carried articles on many aspects of planning systems around the world. We are especially keen to learn about the varying meanings and impact of 'spatial planning' in different places; about why and how planning policies change and the consequences; about citizen engagement in planning; and about the costs and benefits of new tools, methods and technologies in planning. In all this, we value the international comparative sharing of research and practice that puts all places on an equal footing. We will continue to build PPR into a significant resource for practitioners, researchers, teachers and students.

L'Agence Régionale de Développement (ARD) a un statut d’établissement public local à caractère administratif. Elle est placée sous la tutelle technique du Ministère des Collectivités Territoriales, du Développement et de l’Aménagement des Territoires et sous la tutelle Financière du Ministère de l’Economie et des Finances, conformément au décret n° 2012-106 du 18/01/2012 modifié par le décret 2014-1263 du 07 Octobre 2014.
Elle a pour mission générale, l’appui à la coordination et à l'harmonisation des interventions et des initiatives des Collectivités Territoriales en matière de développement local.  
A ce titre l’ARD est chargée de/d’: 
-	l’appui et la facilitation à la planification du développement local ;
-	l’appui à la mise en cohérence des interventions entre collectivités territoriales d'une même région d'une part et avec les politiques et plans nationaux d'autre part ;
-	assurer le suivi-évaluation des programmes et plans d'actions de développement local ;
-	l’appui à la maîtrise d’ouvrage des Collectivités Territoriales ;
-	l’appui à l’exécution des Projets et Programmes ;
-	l’élaboration, l’appui à l’exécution et le suivi des contrats de mise à disposition des services extérieurs de l’Etat ;
-	l’élaboration et le suivi des contrats plans ;
-	l’appui à l’animation, à la mise en œuvre et au suivi des initiatives des Collectivités Territoriales en matière de coopération décentralisée.

Tem como objetivos gerais promover a valorização, divulgação e boas práticas do urbanismo, zelar pelo valor social da sua prática, contribuir para a sua valorização científica e cultural e defender o respeito pelos seus princípios deontológicos.
Tem como objetivos específicos, contribuir para dignificar o exercício da atividade de
urbanismo, nas suas diversas dimensões:
Profissional – apoiando a qualificação dos seus associados e a sua inserção e afirmação
no mercado de trabalho;
Social – promovendo uma cultura de planeamento que salvaguarde o cumprimento
dos princípios e das regras estabelecidas;
Académica – acompanhando as ofertas formativas em urbanismo e avaliando o seu
ajustamento às necessidades práticas emergentes;
Investigação – colocando na agenda temas e desafios concretos que justifiquem um
enquadramento técnico-científico mais personalizado;
Associativa – estreitando e fortalecendo as redes de contacto com outras organizações
congéneres, nacionais e internacionais;
Jurídica – participando na construção de leis e regulamentos que  conduzam a um
ordenamento do território mais sustentável, mais justo e próspero.

Le CERD est une organisation à caractère social et solidaire née de la volonté des membres à contribuer au développement durable de l’Afrique. Créé par déclaration préfectoral N°00000910/RDA/JO6/BAPP du 27 juillet 2015, le CERD comprend un bureau exécutif (instance stratégique) et un sécrétariat permanent (instance opérationnelle). 

NOTRE VISION
Devenir le centre de référence en matière de recherche et de développement en vue d’une Afrique émergente et prospère sur le plan économique, environnemental, social et culturel. 

NOS MISSIONS
-Renforcement des performances stratégiques et opérationnelles des institutions ; 
-Évaluation des programmes et projets ; 
-Formation et entrepreneuriat jeunes ; 
-Amélioration de la qualité des résultats des études statistiques et socio-économiques ; 
-Recherche appliquée et valorisation des résultats de recherche.

NOS VALEURS
Nous avons le même engagement à l'égard des valeurs suivantes : 
 -Esprit d’équipe ;
 -Professionnalisme et rigueur ;
 -Créativité et innovation ;
 -Écoute et service des partenaires.

NOS PRIORITÉS stratégiques
1-Agir à proximité de nos cibles : la proximité est une condition indispensable à la compréhension des besoins de nos cibles afin de mieux orienter nos actions ;
2-Proposer des services personnalisés à la cible : nous développons des offres spécifiques en tenant compte des besoins et attentes de la cible ;
3-Innover pour améliorer nos services et valoriser nos expertises : l’expertise dont dispose le CERD lui permet d’adapter ses offres de services aux évolutions de l’environnement ;
4-Être attentif aux résultats de nos actions : le suivi et l’évaluation de nos actions est un gage de performance au CERD ;
5-Mieux adapter nos actions aux besoins des territoires : l’adaptation aux besoins des territoires est un des leviers pour améliorer l’efficacité ;
6-Faire le pari de la confiance : nous faisons confiance à nos équipes et à nos partenaires ;
7-Renforcer le partenariat : nous disposons un vaste rés

Community Index este agregatorul de Bine pentru comunitate  Credem în puterea implicării companiilor într-o societate care să își poată mobiliza toate părțile interesate pentru a se dezvolta armonios.
Suntem primul index al programelor derulate de companiile din România pentru dezvoltarea comunităților pe diverse paliere:
• sănătate;
• educație;
• mediu;
• sport;
• healthy living;
• sprijin pentru antreprenori;
• protecția animalelor;
• tehnologie.
Totul a plecat de la interesul tot mai mare al companiilor de a aborda domeniul Corporate Social Responsability, aliniat cu dorința noastră de a veni cu exemple de bune practici și studii de caz relevante. 
 Totul pentru beneficii atât pentru comunitate, cât și pentru companiile implicate.

Le Syndicat Mixte pour l’Aménagement de la Plaine de Pierrelaye-Bessancourt (SMAPP) a été créé en 2014 conformément aux dispositions de l’article L. 5721-1 et suivants du Code Général des Collectivités, pour mettre en œuvre le projet d’aménagement forestier. Il regroupe la Région Ile-de-France, le Département du Val-d’Oise, la Communauté d’agglomération Val Parisis (au nom des communes de Bessancourt, Frépillon, Herblay-sur-Seine, Pierrelaye et Taverny,) ainsi que les communes de Méry-sur-Oise et Saint-Ouen l’Aumône.

Le SMAPP, devenu syndicat opérationnel en 2016, s’est vu confier les missions suivantes :

- La réalisation de toutes études, acquisition foncière et tous les travaux directs et indirects nécessaires à la transformation de la Plaine de Pierrelaye Bessancourt en espace naturel, constitué principalement d’une forêt ;
- La création et la gestion de tous les équipements liés à l’exploitation et à l’usage de cet espace ;
- La gestion de la transition de l’espace agricole.

Coast Town Planning (Coast) specialises in providing expert town planning advice and services for development within sensitive coastal environments. Our Town Planners have diverse and extensive experience in development assessment and approvals across the breadth of urban, suburban, commercial, industrial and rural areas of Northern New South Wales and South East Queensland.

Coast offers a premium consulting service, providing development assistance including:
Preliminary  (pre-development) Town Planning advice; 

Preparation of Development Application (DA) documents and reports (Qld and NSW);

Coordination of specialist consultants & Development Assessment process;

Liaison and negotiation with Local and State Government authorities ;

Basic Bushfire Assessment (NSW);

BASIX Certificates;

Preparation of submissions on advertised DAs;

Subdivision, New Builds, Alterations & Additions to existing buildings, and Change of Use of premises.

The Trinidad and Tobago Society of Planners is a professional association committed to promoting spatial, sustainable and inclusive planning principles as an essential means of efficiently allocating public and private resources and sustaining vital communities.
As a learned society, the TTSP strives to be the premier think tank for developing holistic solutions to the complex urban and settlements problems our country faces today and pledges to continuously innovate so as to ensure its members are equipped with the best tools and support necessary to address the emerging developmental issues that our nation will face in the future.
The TTSP has a mandate from its membership to:
- advance the study of spatial planning, civic design and related subjects, and of the arts and sciences as applied to those subjects;
- promote planned, economic, sustainable, aesthetic and culturally relevant development of towns, cities and rural areas;
- champion and lead progress and change in planning practice;
- address issues of importance to the planning profession and/or the public interest;
- act as the authoritative voice and the primary information and knowledge sharing network for planners;
- afford opportunities for continued professional development of its membership; and
- deliver relevant and contemporary benefits and services to its members.

ECO-CITY AFRICA est un bureau d’études, d’appui-conseil et d’ingénierie, spécialisé dans les problématiques urbaines, environnementales, de gestion communale et d’aménagement de territoire.

Notre mission est de fournir une assistance technique par le relèvement du niveau qualitatif des études et réalisations en vue de promouvoir un développement durable en collaboration avec les entreprises privées, les collectivités territoriales et l’administration centrale ainsi que les bailleurs de fonds internationaux et les organismes de coopération.

Nos métiers couvrent divers domaines d’accompagnement au profit de clients du secteur public et privé. Ils concernent en particulier :
- la gestion environnementale : ECOLOG ;
- l’aménagement urbain : ECOPLAN ;
- le bâtiment et les travaux publics : ECOBAT ;
- les outils de gestion communale : GESCOM ;
- les data au service du développement : DATADEV ;
- la formation des acteurs du développement : FORDEV

Pour les maîtres d’ouvrages privés et publics, nous faisons de la gestion de projets, le suivi technique de construction de bâtiments et ouvrages publics, l’évaluation environnementale, le suivi environnemental et HSE des projets d’infrastructures. Nous promettons travailler à vos côtés de sorte à optimiser l’utilisation de vos ressources et garantir la qualité des livrables et des ouvrages. 
Pour les collectivités locales en particulier, nous proposons, outre la planification communale, la mise en place d’outils numériques de gestion urbaine vous permettant, à travers la digitalisation et à la dématérialisation, le suivi de la mise en œuvre des documents de planification, l’amélioration de la mobilisation des ressources locales, l’optimisation de la gestion foncière et la gestion des infrastructures (routières, marchandes, …)

Since 1998 the Global Planning Educators Interest Group has worked under the umbrella of the Association of Collegiate Schools of Planning (ACSP) to bring together planning educators and students from North America to share, shape, and incorporate global perspectives in planning education and research, and to connect with colleagues and partners in other regions of the world. Through its members and ACSP, GPEIG advocates a comparative perspective on planning and development based on a nuanced appreciation of, and respect for, cultural, economic, and socio-political dimensions of planning practices and processes taking shape around the world and influencing our profession worldwide.  We work to ensure that local and regional planning contexts and issues from around the globe enter our comparative frameworks and are treated as critical foundations for effective international planning practice and scholarship. GPEIG also administers and celebrates the work of upcoming scholars through a number of awards including the Gill-Chin Lim Award for the Best Dissertation in International Planning and the Gill-Chin Lim Travel Awards.

GPEIG’s mission is to enable planning educators and students to collaboratively:

Share global perspectives in planning education and research;

Foster an understanding of the global perspectives in planning education and research;

Foster an understanding of the global context of local and regional issues;

Engender an appreciation of and respect for cultural, economic, and political dimensions of planning, and the recognition of the rich array of planning processes that can be fully appreciated only by learning about what is being done in other countries.

The PopUpUrbanSpaces project is a transnational initiative of 10 partners co-financed by the Interreg Central Europe Programme.
A key challenge that hinders making urban mobility systems sustainable is that most people are not willing to abandon cars and shift to a combination of public transport, micro-mobility, and active forms of transport. The overall objective of the project is to enable the public sector and related entities in functional urban areas to encourage changes in the travel behaviour of citizens and to trigger shifts towards smart and sustainable forms of urban mobility by actively involving inhabitants in testing innovative green approaches as well as digital technologies, using tactical urbanism approaches.

The PopUpUrbanSpaces approach is based on the concept of “Show and Tell”: 

- the project enables cities to apply innovative methods based on tactical urbanism/placemaking practices to SHOW citizens (and decision-makers) through pop-up interventions what it would be like to have streets, public spaces not dominated by cars; 

- the project develops innovative digital campaigning tools/methods to TELL (explain) people the risks of car-oriented urban mobility;

The Afro-Heritage Association of Sudbury (AHA) is a registered not-for-profit organization tasked with enhancing the local community by bringing people together and sharing the afro-heritage customs. As part of the intricate tapestry of Canadian multiculturalism, AHA was established in 2005 with a mission to:

1. promote the understanding, communication, cooperation and cultural exchange between Afro-Canadians and other members of the multicultural society;

2. promote unity among the Sudbury community

Municipal Enterprise “Institute of Urban Development” is an innovative organization which impacts crucial spheres of Vinnytsia development:
- international cooperation;
- civil society development and facilitating dialogue between local government
 and civil society organizations;
- ecology and climate change adaptation;
- urban approaches improvement;
- spatial planning improvement.

POW! Strategies, Inc. provides the superpowers to turn-around your town or business with business and economic development services, marketing and communications strategies, management and consultation. We assess your needs, establish a vision and help you set implementable strategies to help you leap tall buildings in a single bound. From there we can help you deliver results that meet your goals, whether through project management, executive management, specific services or solution-oriented plans. 

Overview of Community & Downtown Development Services:
-Comprehensive Strategic Planning - Vision, economic and development, marketing, communications, fundraising, volunteer management, business recruitment and retention; 
-Communications and Marketing Services - market analysis, community engagement, media relations, content and story development, social media and other forms of communications and marketing mediums to reach your audience;
-Executive Management Services - from short-term temporary services to full-service including executive leadership, planning, operations/administration, business recruitment/retention, event management and communications/marketing;
-Business Planning and Start-up Assistance - from direct services for businesses to community programs, such as a retention program or business education.
-Project Management - don't have the time or capacity to manage a project or program - we've got you're back; 
-Site Development - aligning funders, developers and concepts;
-Grant Writing - knowing who to pursue, what funders are looking for and delivering winning grant applications;
-Education and Training - from staff, volunteers to public officials.

Small Business Services
-Business planning and modeling
-Market assessment and site selection
-Business start-up, city permit guidance and assistance
-Brand, communications and marketing strategies and tools

Developer Services
-Site selection
-Community engagement
-City guidance and assistance

Urkiola Landa Garapenaren helburuak landa ingurunearen jasangarritasuna, nekazaritzako elikagaien produkzioa eta eraldakuntza, balio eta garapenean oinarritutako kultura sustatzea, ekonomia lehiakortasuna, erakunde publikoen arau eta jardueren bateratzea, landa-eremuen garapenaren protagonismoa, ondarea berreskuratzea, garatzea eta zabaltzea, lurraldearen antolamendua eta nekazaritzaren lehiakortasuna dira.

//


Urkiola Landa Garapena tiene como objetivos la sostenibilidad del medio rural, la producción y transformación agroalimentaria, el fomento de una cultura basada en valores y desarrollo, la competitividad económica, la armonización de las normas y actividades de las instituciones públicas, el protagonismo del desarrollo de las zonas rurales, la recuperación, desarrollo y difusión del patrimonio, la ordenación del territorio y la competitividad de la agricultura.

Основними завданнями Департаменту є:

- організація заходів з утримання та ремонту об’єктів благоустрою в межах наданих повноважень;
- реалізація державної та муніципальної політики щодо розвитку житлового господарства з питань експлуатації та ремонту багатоквартирних будинків, благоустрою прибудинкової території, виконання ремонтно-будівельних робіт;
- створення та підтримка конкурентного середовища при виробленні та наданні житлово-комунальних послуг;
- сприяння забезпеченню рівних можливостей доступу до отримання мінімальних норм житлово-комунальних послуг для споживачів;
- сприяння дотриманню встановлених стандартів, нормативів, норм, порядків і правил щодо кількості та якості надання житлово-комунальних послуг;
- організація управління об’єктами житлового господарства, що перебувають у комунальній власності, забезпечення їх належного утримання та ефективної експлуатації;
- здійснення контролю за будівництвом та організацією будівництва, ремонту та реконструкції об’єктів житлово-комунального і соціального призначення.

Presque Isle Neighborhood Network (PINN) is a community-led nonprofit organization driving inclusive and comprehensive community and economic development in Millcreek Township, Pennsylvania, with a focus on revitalizing the historic neighborhoods at the foot of Presque Isle State Park into a connected, creative, and thriving place to be.

Our mission is to ultimately foster vibrant, resilient communities where residents can live, work, and belong.  PINN supports place-based initiatives that promote equitable development, affordable housing, civic pride, public spaces, and sustainability, all rooted in the unique identity and potential of our footprint.

We collaborate with residents, businesses, and public partners to:
- Strengthen our footprint's local economy through entrepreneurship and strategic investment;
- Increase access to affordable, quality housing for all;
- Elevate the arts and cultural expression as drivers of community pride and cohesion;
- Advance environmental sustainability, promote walkability and infrastructure, and expand and revitalize public and greenspaces;
- Build civic capacity and deepen community engagement at every step.

PINN was established to create a new model for revitalization that is community-centered, future-facing, and rooted in listening.  We believe the neighborhoods surrounding Presque Isle are poised to become one of the most dynamic destination spots in western Pennsylvania, and we’re building the framework to get there.

Ivano-Frankivsk regional branch of “Association of Ukrainian Cities” is non
profit non-governmental organization, that unites all 62 municipalities of
Ivano-Frankivsk region (Ukraine) and work in the field of development of local
government and promoting local economic development.  
Our goal:  We work to protect and lobby the interests of local self-government, provide expert support, promote regional and international cooperation, create networks among communities, and sustainably develop the Ivano-Frankivsk region.

Our values: 
- Community support;
- Modern, inclusive and socially conscious business practices;
- Open communication with partners, which promotes mutual understanding;
- Team interaction;
- Transparency and accountability;
- Nonpartisanism;
- "Green Office" practice;
- Quality of services.

 Our activities:
- Conducting expert researches and analyses of the regional economy, culture
 and natural environment;
- Providing consultations during the development of Community Development Programs and Strategies, as well as other strategic and promotional documents;
- Assistance to communities in finding international partners and investors;
- Ensuring the participation of partner communities in national and international economic/investment activities;
- Development of cross-border cooperation projects to promote international
 cooperation in Eastern Europe;
- Adaptation of best practices in the field of local self-government development and their implementation in communities of the region;
- Development of tools of open governance and participatory democracy.
